. Says exercise free, fair, credible Former Secretary to the  Ekiti State Government and Governorship aspirant of the All Progressives Congress(APC) Mr. Biofun Abayomi Oyebanji (BAO) has described the primaries as peaceful and credible. Speaking to journalists after participating in the exercise, Oyebanji disclosed that the exercise went on smoothly in many communities stressing that he was not aware of any manipulations or frzud as being insinuated by his coo-contestants. The Governorship hopeful who addressed journalists at his private residence in Ikogosi-Ekiti country home, the APC chieftain declared that the APC appeal panel will handle all controversial issues surrounding the conduct of the election if any. While describing the primary as credible, free, and fair, Oyebanji commended Governor Mohammed Abubakar Badaru-led panel for being thorough in the contest of the shadow poll. “The guidelines of our party give room for the constitution of appeal committee to attend to whatever grievances anyone has. They have the right to their opinions, but the party will come up with its position on whatever they say”. “We thank God for the role of technology in our politics. The reports I got was that things are going on well. I have seen people queuing for accreditation and voted. “In fact, the process has gone on seamlessly and peacefully and the committee should be commended”. POLL : “I know that God will give me victory, because the process has been free and fair and I have done what was expected of me by camapaigning to our people”.Oyebanji  said .